olive oil
1 carrot
2 clove garlic
½ Onion
2 radish
1 tin cannellini beans
1 packet Slivered Almonds
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
20 g butter
1 packet tomato paste
¾ cup water
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet mint
1 packet chicken breast

• Grate the carrot. Finely chop garlic. Thinly slice onion and radish. Drain and rinse cannellini beans..
• Cut chicken breast into 2cm chunks.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Toast slivered almonds, tossing, until golden, 3-4 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

• Return the frying pan to high heat with a generous drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes. Transfer to a bowl and cover to keep warm.
• Return the frying pan to high heat with a generous drizzle of olive oil. Cook carrot and onion until just tender, 2 minutes.
• Add cannellini beans.and cook, tossing occasionally, until golden, 2-3 minutes.
• Add garlic, chermoula spice blend, the butter and tomato paste (see ingredients) and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add the water, stir to combine and simmer until thickened, 1-2 minutes.
• Using a potato masher or fork, lightly mash cannellini beans until some of them have broken up and the sauce has thickened. Season to taste. Remove from heat and set aside.

TIP: Add a splash of water if the cannellini bean mixture looks too thick.

• Heat mini flour tortillas in the microwave in 10 second bursts, until warmed through.
• Bring everything to the table to serve.
• Build your tacos by spreading garlic aioli over tortillas. Top with some baby leaves, chermoula cannellini beans, chicken and radish.
• Top with toasted almonds. Tear over mint leaves to serve. Enjoy!